folder: Centre Street & Cypress Avenue, Queens, NY
text:
Centre Street (junk wagon thereon), north from Cypress to Seneca Aves, showing at the S.E. corner of the last mentioned street Public School No. 77. In the foreground is the Ridgewood Grove, (a place of entertainment.) It was purchased in 1899 by John H. Gerken from Jacob Benner. This is a set of two views.

1922.
View 2: April 1925.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

View1 View2 - Neg # 1234
